  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Safety Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description & Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Identify any unsafe condition or unsafe act carried out on the work site.</li><li>Recommend and assist the Occupier of the worksite to implement reasonable and practicable measures.</li><li>Liaise with different departments on all safety and health matters.</li><li>Conduct regular site inspections and take appropriate corrective actions.</li><li>Ensure compliance with Workplace Safety and Health Regulations and other legislative requirements.</li><li>Enforce all WSH requirements and in-house rules and regulations.</li><li>Assist in investigating and reporting accidents/ incidents and recommend corrective and preventive actions.</li><li>Conduct training/ meeting/ briefing/ time-out to the workforce.</li><li>Follow up on submission of SHE documents.</li><li>Monitor the SHE performance in the work site.</li><li>Performs other duties as assigned.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Certificate in Advanced Certificate in WSH Level B and/or any relevant Safety Certificates.</li><li>With at least 3 years of working experience in high-rise building projects</li><li>Good interpersonal skills.</li><li>This role may require rotating shifts.</li><li>Ability to work under pressure in a fast-paced environment.</li><li>Willing to work night shift</li><li>6 days work week</li></ul>",
